{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase resources to tackle tax evasion and avoidance to help fund UK services",
        "additional_details": "It has been estimated that tax avoidance and evasion costs the UK billions of pounds every year. This is money that could help important services, such as our NHS, which is under extreme pressure due to years of underfunding and the Covid pandemic. Any tax recovered could help to level up the disparity of investment between affluent and neglected communities. The rich minority who can afford the top accountants should not benefit from the complex UK tax loop holes.",
        "background": "The Government should greatly increase the resources allocated to tackling tax evasion and tax avoidance, particularly by large companies and individuals using offshore tax havens. A more robust response should help tackle this injustice.",
